FT  27 MAY 92 / Construction Contracts: Business park scheme
Birmingham Midshires Building Society has appointed four Midlands-based
companies to develop its new Pounds 9m headquarters at Pendeford Business
Park.
Wolverhampton-based Mason Richards Partnership has been appointed as
architects for the project. Clarke Bond Partnership of Birmingham has been
appointed to oversee the structural engineering work. RW Gregory &amp; Partners
has been employed to act as mechanical and electrical engineers. Francis
Groves, another Birmingham-based firm, will act as quantity surveyors.
Birmingham Midshires plans to invite tenders for the main building contract
from a list of nominated companies. A decision on the successful company
will be announced in August.
